Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra and this is Michelle, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi Michelle, Ken Stow here.

Speaker 1: Fidenafil.

Speaker 1: I have a question for you.

Speaker 2: Is there a Viagra AGV or does everything that you have is a generic?

Speaker 1: So it is a generic, but it's the exact same drug as the name brand version,

Speaker 2: but sold without the name brand name on the label.

Speaker 1: And it's marketed with the brand company's permission because we're contracted

Speaker 2: directly with Pfizer with their manufacturing plant called Greenstone.

Speaker 1: That's why you're going to see Greenstone on the bottle because that's the name

Speaker 2: of Pfizer's manufacturer.

Speaker 1: It shares the same active and inactive ingredients.

Speaker 2: It's just less cost.

Speaker 1: Okay, but you market it as Viagra AGV.

Speaker 2: Yes, AGV stands for approved generic Viagra.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So it's not the same as generic.

Speaker 1: It's the exact same as the blue pill, their newest formula,

Speaker 2: because they switched around the inactive ingredients.

Speaker 1: And we do sell the branded Viagra.

Speaker 2: It's just $99 each, and you have to buy a minimum of four.

Speaker 1: So the AGV is exactly the same as Viagra.

Speaker 2: It's just not so expensive.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Well, I was a little confused because, you know,

Speaker 2: in the pictures and everything, it shows Viagra.

Speaker 1: It's not going to say AGV on the pill because that added blue dye is just

Speaker 2: something your body doesn't need, so they took that out a few years ago.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Well, we'll give it a try.

Speaker 2: Yeah, give it a try.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you have me down for can I get off of automatic refill

Speaker 2: and just go with as needed?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: So what you can do is what we did is just pause you for six months.

Speaker 1: That way it keeps your prescription active

Speaker 2: and just allows you to call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 1: Because if we cancel you out completely,

Speaker 2: it's going to delete your profile and then you'd have to sign up.

Speaker 1: And then the doctors, they don't really like that so much

Speaker 2: because we have to pay the doctor's fee every time somebody does that.

Speaker 1: So it's just easier to pause you.

Speaker 2: And then if you don't need a refill, I have you paused until July 31st.

Speaker 1: If you don't need a refill by then, you can just call and pause it further.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So July 31st of this year.

Speaker 1: Yes, correct.

Speaker 2: 2026.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thanks for clarifying that for me.

Speaker 2: Not a problem, Kenneth.

Speaker 1: Not a problem.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Have a great week.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Take care.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye.
